# Vesper ‚Äî Agent Operating Contract

This is the durable contract for AI coding sessions in this repo (Claude Code, opencode, Codex,
Gemini, Cursor). Read it fully before acting. It supersedes assumptions from training; when in
doubt, follow this file.

## Source-of-truth convention (READ FIRST)

The ONLY hand-edited contract files are `.ai/context.md` (this file ‚Äî the project contract) and
`.ai/pipeline.md` (the Vesper cycle, parallel-work, and memory protocol). Everything else is
GENERATED by `bun run sync:ai` (`scripts/sync-ai-docs.ts`) ‚Äî NEVER edit a generated file: your
edit is overwritten on the next sync, and the pre-commit hook blocks committing a stale or
hand-edited one.

- `AGENTS.md` and `.ai/generated/rules.mdc` INLINE the full contract ‚Äî readable everywhere
  (GitHub web view, Codex, any tool without `@`-import support). These are the canonical copies.
- `CLAUDE.md` and `GEMINI.md` are thin `@`-import stubs ‚Äî Claude Code and Gemini CLI resolve
  imports, so the contract is not duplicated into them.
- `.cursor/rules/00-context.mdc` is a symlink to `.ai/generated/rules.mdc`. Onboard another IDE by
  symlinking its rules path to that artifact ‚Äî no script change needed.
- opencode reads `.ai/context.md` + `.ai/pipeline.md` + `.ai/memory.md` directly (`opencode.json`).
- `.claude/`, `.opencode/`, `.gemini/` agents + skills are materialized copies of `.ai/agents/` +
  `.ai/skills/` (gitignored; each developer regenerates with `bun run sync:ai`).
- `specs/` are **LOCAL-only working drafts** (gitignored ‚Äî like `.ai/memory.md`): they are NOT
  committed or distributed, so a GitHub clone never ships them. The committed, shared record of a
  cycle is the **commit message + `cycle-log.md`**, never `specs/`. Treat `specs/<feature>.md` as a
  private design scratchpad; durable decisions graduate into this contract and `cycle-log.md`.

To change a convention: edit `.ai/context.md` or `.ai/pipeline.md`, run `bun run sync:ai`, and
commit the regenerated entry files. A change that leaves the generated docs stale (no re-sync) is
incomplete and the pre-commit hook will reject it.

