### Linear status protocol (every cycle step transitions the issue)

Omar reads Linear to know where work is. Silent progress is invisible progress. Move status and
post a comment at every step. Map to the closest available workflow state. (The cycle steps these
rows reference are defined in `.ai/pipeline.md`.)

| Cycle step | Linear status | Required comment |
|---|---|---|
| Pre-start | Todo / Backlog | (initial) |
| SPEC | In Progress | `SPEC started ‚Äî proposal at specs/<feature>.md` |
| PLAN | In Progress | `PLAN ready ‚Äî N tasks` |
| BUILD | In Progress | `BUILD started` + per-task `task N/M complete` |
| TEST | In Review | `TEST passed ‚Äî coverage X%` OR `TEST failed ‚Äî returning to BUILD` |
| REVIEW | In Review | `REVIEW complete ‚Äî no deviations` OR `REVIEW found deltas ‚Äî see comment` |
| SIMPLIFY | In Review | `SIMPLIFY complete ‚Äî N lines removed, tests still green` |
| IMPROVE | In Review | `IMPROVE captured ‚Äî see deltas` OR `IMPROVE ‚Äî no deltas, pattern held` |
| SHIP/DELEGATE | Done (ship) / Done + new issue (delegate) | `SHIPPED ‚Äî commit <sha>` OR `DELEGATED ‚Üí DEV-NNN` |
| REPEAT | (next issue Todo‚ÜíIn Progress) | (begins next issue's SPEC) |

Rules: if returning to a prior step (TEST fails ‚Üí BUILD), post `REVERTED to BUILD ‚Äî <reason>`.
Forking into multiple issues requires Omar's authorization first. On SHIP, move to Done only
after the commit lands. Don't delegate into the void ‚Äî the downstream issue must already exist.
If Linear MCP is unavailable (or its issue cap is hit), write transitions to `cycle-log.md` as a
