## Memory protocol (three coexisting layers ‚Äî do not merge them)

1. **`.ai/memory.md`** ‚Äî a LOCAL, per-developer working log shared across the AI CLIs on your
   machine (Claude Code, opencode, Codex, Gemini). It is **gitignored**, seeded from the committed
   template `.ai/memory.example.md` (auto-seeded by `bun run sync:ai`). Referenced via
   `@.ai/memory.md`, never inlined into committed files. APPEND, never rewrite; terse entries,
   newest at the bottom of `## Log`. Shapes: `### [YYYY-MM-DD] build-error` (`symptom ‚Üí root cause
   ‚Üí fix`) and `### [YYYY-MM-DD] gotcha` (a runtime/library quirk found the hard way).
2. **claude-mem** ‚Äî machine-level, cross-session user/project memory (MCP). Not in this repo.
3. **`cycle-log.md`** ‚Äî committed IMPROVE-step reflections, one entry per completed cycle.

DURABLE, team-facing decisions do NOT go in `.ai/memory.md`. They go in the commit message, the
Linear issue, `cycle-log.md`, and/or a short ADR under `docs/adr/` ‚Äî reviewed and committed.
`.ai/memory.md` is for ephemeral, per-dev working notes only.

**NEVER write a secret** into `.ai/memory.md` (Keychain values, GitHub tokens, Discord webhooks,
API keys) ‚Äî even though it is local and gitignored, the example template is committed and the
habit leaks.

## Memory

Shared working log: `.ai/memory.md` ‚Äî LOCAL and gitignored (seed from
`.ai/memory.example.md`; `bun run sync:ai` seeds it for you). It is not inlined here;
